CHAPTER XXXIX.

Philip, learning that tho Ambassadors and Letters had fallen into the Hands of tho Romans, sends other Ambassadors to Hannibal. These reach Hannibal and return in Safety. Fabius crosses tho Volturnus, and takes joint Action with his Colleaguo. Combulteria, Trebula, and Austicula, revolted citios, retaken. Tho Pcoplo of Nola meditate tho Destruction of their principal Men. Fabius encamps abore Suessula. M. Marcellus sent to occupy Nola.— n.c. 215.
